HEADWORD: Lapdog
<hw>Lap"dog`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A small
dog which is or can be fondled in the lap.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who does the bidding of another; a servile
follower.</def> <mark>[informal]</mark> ⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lapel</ent>⟦br⟧
